ARMENIA 
Mr. Sarkis Assadourian ( Brampton Centre , Lib . ) : 
Mr. Speaker , I rise in the House today to commemorate the 80 th anniversary of Armenian independence . 
on May 28 , 1918 the Armenian nation threw off the shackles of oppression of the Ottoman Empire and re - established itself as an independent nation on the world stage . 
today Armenians throughout the world join together to celebrate the birth of the modern Armenian state . 
as we gather to celebrate this important milestone we will pray that the growth of democracy and the rule of law will continue to flourish in today ' s Armenia . 
Armenians have fought countless battles and endured immeasurable hardships to sustain our language and culture and , in fact , our very existence as a nation . 
happy Anniversary , Armenia . 
